        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 25</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num025-P256r-L20_trl" n="20"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.004.024.trl.xml#Num024-P256r-L20_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             Israel stayed in Shittim, and the people began to fall into harlotry
                            with the daughters
                            <milestone unit="page" n="256v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             of Moab.</l>
                        <l n="2">And they called the people to the sacrifices
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             of their gods, and the people ate and worshiped to their gods.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="3">And Israel joined the service of Baal of Peor.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             And the anger of the Lord was kindled against Israel.</l>
                        <l n="4">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             the Lord said to Moses, ‘Take all the elders of the people
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             together and <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-025-seg001_trl" />bury
                            them alive<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-025-seg001_trl" /><ref
                                n="1" target="#Num-025-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-025-seg002_trl" />before the Lord,
                            the ones
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             who joined the service of Baal of Peor<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-025-seg002_trl" /><ref n="2" target="#Num-025-fn2_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />, and they shall be in
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             the sun, and the furious anger of the Lord will be turned away
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             from Israel.’</l>
                        <l n="4">And Moses said to the judges of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             ‘Each of you kill those of his men who were joined
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             to Baal of Peor.’</l>
                        <l n="6">And, lo, one man of the children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             of Israel came and brought to his brothers
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             a Midianite woman in the sight of Moses and in the sight
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of all the congregation of the children of Israel, and they wept
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             before the door of the tent of meeting.</l>
                        <l n="7">And Phinehas,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             son of Eleazar, son of Aaron, the priest, saw, and he rose
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             from among the congregation and took a spear in his hand.</l>
                        <l n="8">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             And he came after the man of Israel to the chamber, and he pierced
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             both of them, the man of Israel and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             woman, to her stomach. So the plague was stayed from the children of
                            Israel.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                        <l n="9">And those who died by the plague were twenty-
                            <milestone unit="page" n="257r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             -four thousand.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            <emph>Parashat Pinchas</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="10">And the Lord spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="11">‘Phinehas,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             son of Eleazar, son of Aaron, the priest,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             has turned my fury from the children of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             in that he was jealous for my jealousy among
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             them, so that I did not consume the children of Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             in my jealousy.</l>
                        <l n="12">Therefore say, “Lo, I
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             give to him my covenant of peace.</l>
                        <l n="13">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             And it will be his and his offspring’s after him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             the covenant of an eternal priesthood, because he was jealous
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             for his God, and he asked for atonement for the children of
                            Israel.”’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="14">And the name of the Israelite man who was killed,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             who was killed with <addSpan spanTo="#Num-025-add001_trl"
                                 /><emph>the</emph><anchor type="addSpan"
                                xml:id="Num-025-add001_trl" /> Midianite woman, was Zimri,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             son of Salu, prince of a fathers’ house of the tribe of the Simeon.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="15">And the name of the <supplied reason="lost">Midianite</supplied>
                            woman who was killed was Cozbi,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             daughter of Zur, the superior of people of a father’s house in
                            Midian.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="16">And the Lord spoke to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             saying,</l>
                        <l n="17">‘Oppress the Midianites
                            <milestone unit="page" n="257v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             and break them.</l>
                        <l n="18">Because they oppressed you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             with their evil thoughts, with which they have done evil thoughts to
                            you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             in the matter of Peor, and in the matter of Cozbi, the daughter of a
                            prince
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             of Midian, their sister who was killed in the day of the plague
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num025-P257v-L5_trl" n="5"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.026.trl.xml#Num026-P257v-L5_trl" />
                             over the matter of Peor.’ </l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
